<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
LM (
<figureCitation box="[211,335,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 2–15</figureCitation>
): Valves lanceolate with long protracted capitate apices (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1130,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 2–15</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[1233,1356,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="72.5" valueMax="83.0" valueMin="62.0">62–83 µm</quantity>
, width 9.2–12.0 µ m. Raphe moderately lateral, becoming filiform at distal ends, with strongly unilaterally deflected (hooked) distal ends. Axial area narrow, linear. Shape of central area varies from narrow rectangular (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 2– 3, 5–6, 10–13</figureCitation>
) to asymmetrical stauros expanding towards valve margins (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1112,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1049,1071]" captionTargetBox="[305,1283,201,1017]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[304,1284,197,1025]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1: Geographical location of the study sites. Lake Xiaolongwan is marked by an X, Sifangshan Tianchi by a S. Shaded areas represent mountainous regions with an elevation&gt;1000 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100397/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1128,1295,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">4, 7–9, 14–15</figureCitation>
). Shortened striae may be present at valve margins (
<figureCitation box="[639,856,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 2, 5–8, 9–12</figureCitation>
) or not (
<figureCitation box="[963,1167,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[329,1257,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-60@3.[329,1257,197,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Light micro-photographs of Stauroneis lacusvulcani. Scale bar = 10 µm. Figs 3,4,7,8. Specimen from Sifangshan Tianchi, surface-sediment. Figs 2, 5, 6. Specimens from Xialongwan surface-sediment. Figs 9–15. Specimens from Xiaolongwan core sample." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 3–4, 13–15</figureCitation>
). Striae parallel along border of stauros becoming radiate to more steeply radiate near valve apices, 
<quantity box="[1058,1160,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.223" metricValueMax="7.112" metricValueMin="5.334" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="in" value="24.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="21.0">21–28 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[1167,1247,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
SEM (
<figureCitation box="[276,415,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,603,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-245@4.[233,1354,603,1926]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. SEM of Stauroneis lacusvulcani from Sifangshan. 16. Exterior view of whole valve. 17. Close-up of valve centre. 18. Close-up of distal end. 19. Interior view of whole valve. 20. Interior view of centre showing ridge bearing raphe fissure. 21. Interior view of distal end showing helictoglossa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 16–21</figureCitation>
): Areolae round to transapically oblong, irregularly spaced, 
<quantity box="[1137,1243,384,410]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" metricValueMax="7.112" metricValueMin="4.572" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="in" value="23.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="18.0">18–28 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[1252,1333,384,410]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
. Weakly developed hyaline area present, thus striae next to stauros appear discontinuous (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1229,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,603,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-245@4.[233,1354,603,1926]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. SEM of Stauroneis lacusvulcani from Sifangshan. 16. Exterior view of whole valve. 17. Close-up of valve centre. 18. Close-up of distal end. 19. Interior view of whole valve. 20. Interior view of centre showing ridge bearing raphe fissure. 21. Interior view of distal end showing helictoglossa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Figs 17, 20</figureCitation>
). Raphe bordered by wide sternum on each side. Proximal raphe ends straight and slightly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1238,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,603,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-245@4.[233,1354,603,1926]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. SEM of Stauroneis lacusvulcani from Sifangshan. 16. Exterior view of whole valve. 17. Close-up of valve centre. 18. Close-up of distal end. 19. Interior view of whole valve. 20. Interior view of centre showing ridge bearing raphe fissure. 21. Interior view of distal end showing helictoglossa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), apical external raphe endings hooked with hooks opening toward secondary side (
<figureCitation box="[951,1041,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,603,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-245@4.[233,1354,603,1926]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. SEM of Stauroneis lacusvulcani from Sifangshan. 16. Exterior view of whole valve. 17. Close-up of valve centre. 18. Close-up of distal end. 19. Interior view of whole valve. 20. Interior view of centre showing ridge bearing raphe fissure. 21. Interior view of distal end showing helictoglossa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Internally, raphe-sternum bears longitudinal ribs and well-developed helictoglossae (
<figureCitation box="[770,858,538,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,603,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-245@4.[233,1354,603,1926]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. SEM of Stauroneis lacusvulcani from Sifangshan. 16. Exterior view of whole valve. 17. Close-up of valve centre. 18. Close-up of distal end. 19. Interior view of whole valve. 20. Interior view of centre showing ridge bearing raphe fissure. 21. Interior view of distal end showing helictoglossa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
